==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pursy
<hw>Pur"sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>pourcif</ets>, <ets>poulsif</ets>, <ets>poussif</ets>, fr.
<ets>pousser</ets> to push, thrust, heave, OF. also <ets>poulser</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>pousse</ets> the heaves, asthma. See <er>Push</er>.]</ety>
<def>Fat and short-breathed; fat, short, and thick; swelled with
pampering; <as>as, <ex>pursy</ex> insolence</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pursy</qex> important he sat him down.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

